  "body": "# TEST CASE:\r\n\r\n1. Fork this repo\r\n2. `bundle install`\r\n3. Edit any EIP and add `Hello, $x = y$` in the text\r\n4. `bundle exec jekyll serve`\r\n5. Load the page in your browser\r\n6. View relevant source\r\n\r\n# EXPECTED\r\n\r\nThe math equation is visible in all its TeX glory.\r\n\r\n# ACTUAL\r\n\r\nThe source shows the code as `<script type=\"math/tex; mode=display\">x = y</script>`, but it is not rendered in the browser.\r\n\r\n# IMPACT\r\n\r\nWe are using math expressions in EIPs and TeX is the prettiest and most common way to render math expressions in academic publications.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n# SOLUTION\r\n\r\nCurrently we use the vendor-provided gitbub-pages default.html layout. Please see the comments in `Gemfile` and do the commenting and uncommenting of lines (and rerun `bundle install`) to get the GitHub environment running on your computer.\r\n\r\nWe may need to copy-paste default.html into this repo's `_layouts` directory to make changes. Then we can add a script https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.5/MathJax.js into there. This should cause it to render properly.",
