    "body": "It’s not the GitHub pages default it’s the Jekyll default theme “minima” and yes it would need to be included in _layouts to be edited. \n\nDid some reading on this: https://quuxplusone.github.io/blog/2018/08/05/mathjax-in-jekyll/\n\nAlso, Kramdown (the rendering engine) May already support this? See https://kramdown.gettalong.org/syntax.html\n\nThis should test it:\n```\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n  & \\phi(x,y) = \\phi \\left(\\sum_{i=1}^n x_ie_i, \\sum_{j=1}^n y_je_j \\right)\n  = \\sum_{i=1}^n \\sum_{j=1}^n x_i y_j \\phi(e_i, e_j) = \\\\\n  & (x_1, \\ldots, x_n) \\left( \\begin{array}{ccc}\n      \\phi(e_1, e_1) & \\cdots & \\phi(e_1, e_n) \\\\\n      \\vdots & \\ddots & \\vdots \\\\\n      \\phi(e_n, e_1) & \\cdots & \\phi(e_n, e_n)\n    \\end{array} \\right)\n  \\left( \\begin{array}{c}\n      y_1 \\\\\n      \\vdots \\\\\n      y_n\n    \\end{array} \\right)\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n```",
